---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Texas Trucking Insurance | New Authority Specialists | RMS" description="Licensed Texas trucking insurance for owner-operators and new authorities. 5-minute COIs, same-day quotes. 1,000+ truckers helped. Get your Texas quote today.">

  <!-- Schema Markup -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "InsuranceAgency",
    "name": "RMS Truck Insurance",
    "description": "Texas trucking insurance specialists for owner-operators and new authorities",
    "areaServed": {
      "@type": "State",
      "name": "Texas"
    },
    "telephone": "+1-208-800-0640",
    "url": "https://rmstruckers.com/trucking-insurance-texas/",
    "knowsAbout": ["commercial trucking insurance", "new authority insurance", "Texas trucking"],
    "slogan": "Finally, someone on your side."
  }
  </script>

  <!-- FAQ Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does Texas trucking insurance cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For new authorities, expect $12,000-$18,000/year for a single truck with $750K liability. Rates depend on your experience, driving record, equipment, and cargo. Get a quote to see your actual numbers."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can RMS insure new trucking companies?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes - that's our specialty. Most agencies avoid new authorities because they're harder to place. We've built our business on helping new truckers get started."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How fast can I get a quote?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Same day for most operations. Complex risks (hazmat, specialized cargo) may take 24-48 hours to shop properly."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What if I'm doing cross-border work to Mexico?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "We handle it. Laredo, El Paso, Brownsville - we know the coverage requirements for cross-border operations."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <div class="state-badge">
        <span class="state-flag">&#9733;</span>
        <span>Licensed in Texas</span>
      </div>

      <h1>Texas Trucking Insurance</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">Licensed. Specialized. Fast.</p>

      <p class="hero-sub">RMS helps Texas truckers get insured and on the road. New authority? Established carrier? We've got you covered in the Lone Star State.</p>

      <div class="trust-badges">
        <div class="badge"><span class="badge-icon">&#10003;</span> Licensed in Texas</div>
        <div class="badge"><span class="badge-icon">&#10003;</span> 1,000+ Truckers Helped</div>
        <div class="badge"><span class="badge-icon">&#10003;</span> 5-Minute COIs</div>
        <div class="badge"><span class="badge-icon">&#10003;</span> Trucking Specialists Since 2020</div>
      </div>

      <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="hero-cta">
        <span class="cta-label">Get Your Texas Quote</span>
        <span class="cta-number">208-800-0640</span>
      </a>

      <p class="hero-note">New authority? We handle the 20-21 day wait period timing.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TEXAS REQUIREMENTS -->
  <section class="requirements">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">What You Need</span>
        <h2>Texas Insurance Requirements</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">Texas has specific requirements depending on whether you're staying in-state or crossing state lines. Here's the quick breakdown:</p>
      </div>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="req-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Your Operation</th>
              <th>Minimum Liability</th>
              <th>What You Need</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Interstate (most truckers)</td>
              <td><strong>$750,000</strong></td>
              <td>USDOT + MC Number</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Texas-only, general freight</td>
              <td><strong>$500,000</strong></td>
              <td>USDOT + TxDMV Number</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Texas-only, household goods</td>
              <td><strong>$300,000-$500,000</strong></td>
              <td>USDOT + TxDMV Number</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Hazmat</td>
              <td><strong>$5,000,000</strong></td>
              <td>Special permits</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="section-cta">
        <p>Not sure which category you fall into? That's what we're here for. We'll figure out exactly what you need - no more, no less.</p>
        <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="btn">Call 208-800-0640</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY RMS -->
  <section class="why-rms">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">Why RMS</span>
        <h2>Why Texas Truckers Choose Us</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-box">
        <p class="problem"><strong>The Problem:</strong> For new trucking companies, your options are limited. Progressive, Berkshire, GEICO - that's basically it for the first two years. The price is roughly the same no matter who you go through.</p>
        <p class="insight"><em>"You're not shopping for a policy - you're shopping for an agent."</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="value-grid">
        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>Trucking Specialists Only</h3>
          <p>We don't sell home or auto. We know trucking inside and out.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>New Authority Experts</h3>
          <p>We've helped 1,000+ truckers through the 20-21 day FMCSA wait. We time your insurance perfectly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>5-Minute COIs</h3>
          <p>When a broker needs your certificate NOW, we deliver. Texas freight moves fast.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>10-Minute Federal Filings</h3>
          <p>Your BMC-91 and BOC-3 filed within minutes of binding.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>Licensed in Texas</h3>
          <p>Stewart Hyndman holds our Texas license. We know TxDMV and FMCSA.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card highlight">
          <h3>"Finally, someone on your side."</h3>
          <p>That's not just a tagline. It's how we do business.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-cta centered">
        <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="btn">Get Your Texas Quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TEXAS MARKET -->
  <section class="texas-market">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">The Market</span>
        <h2>Texas - The Biggest Trucking Market</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="market-content">
        <div class="market-text">
          <p>Texas has <strong>66,000+ trucking companies</strong> - more than any other state. That means:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>More freight opportunities (2.1 billion tons moved annually)</li>
            <li>More competition for loads</li>
            <li>More brokers who need your COI fast</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="corridors">
          <h3>The Corridors That Matter</h3>
          <div class="corridor-list">
            <div class="corridor">
              <span class="corridor-name">I-35</span>
              <span class="corridor-route">Laredo → Dallas</span>
              <p>40% of all US-Mexico trade. Busiest inland port in North America.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="corridor">
              <span class="corridor-name">I-10</span>
              <span class="corridor-route">El Paso → Houston</span>
              <p>Port Houston imports, coast-to-coast freight.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="corridor">
              <span class="corridor-name">Texas Triangle</span>
              <span class="corridor-route">Dallas • Houston • San Antonio</span>
              <p>70% of Texas logistics concentrated here.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-cta">
        <p>Running I-35 or I-10? We know these corridors. We know the coverage you need for cross-border work, port deliveries, and everything in between.</p>
        <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="btn">Talk to a Texas Specialist</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NEW AUTHORITY PROCESS -->
  <section class="new-authority">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">New Authorities</span>
        <h2>Starting a Trucking Company in Texas?</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Day 1</span>
          <p>Apply for USDOT and MC numbers ($300 FMCSA fee)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Days 1-17</span>
          <p>20-21 day waiting period begins</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <span class="day">Day 18</span>
          <p>RMS binds your insurance, files your BMC-91 within 10 minutes</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Day 21</span>
          <p>Your authority goes active. You're legal to haul.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rms-difference">
        <h3>The RMS Difference</h3>
        <p>We've done this 1,000+ times. We know exactly when to bind so you're not paying for insurance days you can't use, but your filings hit FMCSA in time.</p>
        <p><strong>Texas-specific:</strong> If you're doing Texas-only (intrastate), you'll also need a TxDMV number. Different process, 3-10 days. We'll guide you through both if needed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="section-cta centered">
        <p>Starting a trucking company in Texas? Let's talk through your timeline.</p>
        <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="btn">Call 208-800-0640</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COVERAGE OPTIONS -->
  <section class="coverage">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Coverage</span>
        <h2>What Texas Truckers Typically Need</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="coverage-grid">
        <div class="coverage-card required">
          <span class="coverage-badge">Required</span>
          <h3>Auto Liability</h3>
          <p>Damage/injury you cause to others. $750K minimum for interstate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="coverage-card">
          <span class="coverage-badge">If Financed</span>
          <h3>Physical Damage</h3>
          <p>Your truck - collision, theft, fire. Required by most lenders.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="coverage-card">
          <span class="coverage-badge">Usually</span>
          <h3>Cargo Insurance</h3>
          <p>The freight you're hauling. Most brokers require it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="coverage-card">
          <span class="coverage-badge">Sometimes</span>
          <h3>General Liability</h3>
          <p>Non-trucking incidents. Required by some brokers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="coverage-card">
          <span class="coverage-badge">Optional</span>
          <h3>Bobtail / NTL</h3>
          <p>Driving without a trailer. Covers off-dispatch driving.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="coverage-approach">
        <p><strong>Our approach:</strong> We don't upsell coverage you don't need. We figure out what's required, what's smart, and what's optional - then let you decide.</p>
        <p class="carriers">Carriers we work with: Progressive, Berkshire Hathaway, GEICO, Artisan & Truckers, United Financial</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-layout">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <span class="section-tag">FAQ</span>
          <h2>Texas Trucking Insurance Questions</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How much does Texas trucking insurance cost?</summary>
            <p>For new authorities, expect $12,000-$18,000/year for a single truck with $750K liability. Rates depend on your experience, driving record, equipment, and cargo. Get a quote to see your actual numbers.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Can RMS insure new trucking companies?</summary>
            <p>Yes - that's our specialty. Most agencies avoid new authorities because they're harder to place. We've built our business on helping new truckers get started.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How fast can I get a quote?</summary>
            <p>Same day for most operations. Complex risks (hazmat, specialized cargo) may take 24-48 hours to shop properly.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What if I'm doing cross-border work to Mexico?</summary>
            <p>We handle it. Laredo, El Paso, Brownsville - we know the coverage requirements for cross-border operations.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>I already have insurance but want to switch. Can you help?</summary>
            <p>Absolutely. We'll quote you, and if we can beat your current rate or offer better service, we'll handle the switch. No pressure.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OTHER STATES -->
  <section class="other-states">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">Also Serving</span>
        <h2>Trucking Insurance in Other States</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="states-grid">
        <a href="/trucking-insurance-illinois/" class="state-link">Illinois</a>
        <a href="/trucking-insurance-ohio/" class="state-link">Ohio</a>
        <a href="/trucking-insurance-pennsylvania/" class="state-link">Pennsylvania</a>
        <a href="/trucking-insurance-georgia/" class="state-link">Georgia</a>
      </div>
      <p class="states-note">Licensed in 40+ states. <a href="/">See all coverage areas</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FINAL CTA -->
  <section class="final-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Get Your Texas Trucking Insurance?</h2>
      <p>Whether you're a new authority waiting on FMCSA or an established owner-operator shopping rates, RMS is here to help.</p>

      <div class="cta-options">
        <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="cta-phone">
          <span class="cta-type">Call</span>
          <span class="cta-value">208-800-0640</span>
        </a>
        <a href="sms:208-800-0644" class="cta-text">
          <span class="cta-type">Text</span>
          <span class="cta-value">208-800-0644</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="trust-close">1,000+ truckers helped. Licensed in 40 states. Trucking specialists since 2020.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MOBILE STICKY -->
  <div class="mobile-cta">
    <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="mobile-btn">Get Texas Quote - 208-800-0640</a>
  </div>

</Layout>

<style>
  :root {
    --forest: #1B4332;
    --forest-deep: #0D2118;
    --gold: #DAA520;
    --gold-hover: #B8860B;
    --white: #ffffff;
    --gray-100: #f7f7f7;
    --gray-200: #e5e5e5;
    --gray-600: #6b7280;
    --text: #1f2937;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .section-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .section-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section-header.centered {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--forest);
  }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray-600);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--gold);
    color: var(--forest-deep);
    padding: 14px 28px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--forest);
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .section-cta {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--gray-100);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
  }

  .section-cta.centered {
    text-align: center;
    border-left: none;
    border-top: 4px solid var(--gold);
  }

  .section-cta p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* HERO */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    padding: 7rem 2rem 5rem;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: var(--forest-deep);
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .hero-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .state-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    background: rgba(218,165,32,0.15);
    border: 1px solid rgba(218,165,32,0.3);
    padding: 8px 16px;
    border-radius: 50px;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .state-flag { font-size: 1rem; }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 6vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .hero-tagline {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    opacity: 0.85;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .trust-badges {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .badge {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .badge-icon {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .hero-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--gold);
    color: var(--forest-deep);
    padding: 1.25rem 3rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-cta:hover {
    background: var(--white);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .cta-label {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    opacity: 0.7;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }

  .cta-number {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .hero-note {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* REQUIREMENTS */
  .requirements {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--white);
  }

  .table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .req-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }

  .req-table th,
  .req-table td {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
  }

  .req-table th {
    background: var(--forest);
    color: var(--white);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .req-table th:first-child { border-radius: 4px 0 0 0; }
  .req-table th:last-child { border-radius: 0 4px 0 0; }

  .req-table td {
    background: var(--gray-100);
  }

  /* WHY RMS */
  .why-rms {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--gray-100);
  }

  .problem-box {
    background: var(--white);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .problem {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .insight {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--forest);
  }

  .value-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .value-card {
    background: var(--white);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
  }

  .value-card.highlight {
    background: var(--forest);
    border-color: var(--forest);
  }

  .value-card.highlight h3,
  .value-card.highlight p {
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .value-card.highlight h3 {
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .value-card p {
    color: var(--gray-600);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* TEXAS MARKET */
  .texas-market {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--forest-deep);
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .texas-market .section-header h2 {
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .market-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .market-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .market-text ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .market-text li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .corridors h3 {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .corridor-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .corridor {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
  }

  .corridor-name {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .corridor-route {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .corridor p {
